name: Simon Fraser University - Harbour Centre
directions: If you enter SFU Harbour Centre from the Hastings St entrance go straight in and then turn left (by the security office) and continue down that hallway until you see the washrooms, which will be on the left. There are two gendered washrooms and one single stall handicap washroom.
comment: As this is a university campus it's extremely unlikely anyone will notice you coming in to use the washroom or give you a hard time. Security has always been friendly to me.

name: Far from the Tree Cider

name: Oregon Wine Lab

name: Starbucks
directions: Back of store
comment: All starbucks bathrooms are single use. And at this location the team is very open and consider this bathrooms safe and for all genders regardless of the sign that's next to the door. And if you do feel unsafe at all just let them know.

name: Family Eye Clinic
directions:
Right at the front entrance
2 separate single stall "family" restaurants
comment:
Theoretically just for patients (or customers looking for glasses frames), but the front desk can't see you until you're further inside the building.  No automatic door opener, but might accommodate wheelchair turn radius.  Changing table inside.

Double check hours at 303eyetest.com, they are weird and change frequently to accommodate evening and weekend appointments.
